<TITLE> JU professor shot, mugged </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, Jan 18 (bdnews24.com)  Muggers shot a Jahangirnagar University professor, stealing Tk 5 lakh from him on Monday, police said. Four men riding two motorcycles opened fire at Prof Ayub Ali Khan of JU's archaeology department in front of the Savar sub-registrar's office at around 4pm, police sub inspector Abu Taher told bdnews24.com. The muggers fled on their motorbikes after the robbery. Locals rescued the shot professor from the spot, taking him to the Savar Enam Medical College Hospital. He was later transferred to Dhaka Medical College Hospital as his condition worsened, said the Savar sub inspector. bdne
